> This tasty trout dish is our twist on meunière, the simple French method of cooking fish to bright, buttery perfection. You'll coat fillets in seasoned flour, then pan-fry in a hot skillet until golden and serve with a lemony scallion-parsley crème fraîche sauce—the perfect pairing! To complete the meal are sides of garlicky almond-studded rice pilaf and tender roasted green beans.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

== Lemon-Almond Rice Pilaf ==

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot over medium-high heat. Add @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and garlic and cook, stirring, until golden and fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Green Beans ==

While rice cooks, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss green beans on a #baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until tender and browned, ~{12-15%minutes}. Remove sheet from #oven; carefully cover with #foil to keep warm.

== Creamy Herb Sauce ==

Trim and mince @scallions{2}. Mince @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl, combine scallions, parsley, @crème fraîche{2%tablespoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lemon juice; season with salt and pepper to taste. Set aside.

== Pan-Seared Trout ==

Pat @steelhead trout{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. In a #shallow bowl, combine @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, half the @flour{1/2%cup}, ½ tsp salt, and a pinch of pepper (all the flour and 1 tsp salt for 4 servings).

Add trout to bowl with flour mixture and turn to coat, shaking off any excess.

> Trout is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Cooking the Trout ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan over medium heat. Add coated trout to pan, skin sides down.

Cook until skin is crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}. Flip and cook until trout is golden and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} more. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice pilaf with a #fork. Stir in lemon zest.

Spoon a layer of creamy herb sauce on one side of each plate. Arrange trout over sauce. Divide rice pilaf and green beans between plates in separate sections. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.